Failed Experiments & Pivots (Critical for IRS)
Experiment 1: Gamification Without CLT
Hypothesis: Traditional gamification (badges, leaderboards, streaks) will increase engagement
Duration: 35 hours
Result: FAILED - Users felt stressed, completion rates dropped 22%
Learning: Gamification adds cognitive load; must be CLT-optimized or removed
QRE: $3,500 ✅

Experiment 2: Long-Form Video Content
Hypothesis: YouTube-style 20-40 min videos with community features
Duration: 40 hours
Result: FAILED - 78% drop-off before completion; users reported feeling overwhelmed
Learning: Short-form content (5-10 min) matches attention span + cognitive capacity
QRE: $4,000 ✅

Experiment 3: Pure Algorithmic Feed (No User Control)
Hypothesis: AI should decide all content delivery to optimize learning
Duration: 30 hours
Result: FAILED - Users felt "controlled," satisfaction scores dropped
Learning: Autonomy is critical; agents should suggest, not dictate
QRE: $3,000 ✅

